### AMS2025 school Zagreb, day 1, exercise 3:
### Simulation of a Lennard-Jones system.
###
### 

### how often to print output data; each Nprint steps
variable Nprint  equal 500

units           lj
atom_style      atomic

### read input structure from file:
###   the structure contains 1000 atoms in a simple cubic lattice
###   with side length 10.0, thus the particle density is 1.0
read_data       lj_box.lmp

### give a small displacement to initial positions,
### to break the configuration symmetry
#displace_atoms  all random 0.05 0.05 0.05 1234

mass            1 1.0


### select Berendsen thermostat, last 3 values set the temperature:
### T_start  T_end  T_damp
fix             2 all temp/berendsen   1.0   1.0   2.0

### specify the LJ potential with a cutoff
pair_style      lj/cut 2.5
### parameters for LJ: 
### type_i type_j epsilon sigma cutoff
pair_coeff      1 1 1.0 1.0 2.5

neighbor        0.3 bin
neigh_modify    every 20 delay 0 check no

### select NVE ensemble
fix             1 all nve

compute         epot all pe/atom
compute         ekin all ke/atom

### dump the structure every Nprint simulation steps into file
dump            1 all custom ${Nprint} dump.dat id type x y z vx vy vz fx fy fz c_epot c_ekin

thermo_style    custom step temp press pe ke etotal

### write thermodynamics data to screen every Nprint steps
thermo          ${Nprint}

### delta t parameter: default = 0.005
#timestep 0.008

### run the simulation for N steps
run             80000
